00:25:32,072 --> 00:25:36,390
So the, the weight loss is, is an amazing
feature right up front, and

381
00:25:36,390 --> 00:25:40,120
it makes you feel incredibly weak doing
that.

382
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:44,569
At lesser elevations, where you don't tend
to lose so much muscle mass.

383
00:25:45,860 --> 00:25:51,640
One of the amazing features is how that
adaptation of

384
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:55,710
higher elevation exposure makes your body
run really well.

385
00:25:55,710 --> 00:25:59,890
I mean, you get a, a beneficial adaptive
response,

386
00:25:59,890 --> 00:26:05,580
which is why so many category one cyclists
now live in Boulder, Colorado.

387
00:26:05,580 --> 00:26:10,400
Because they get to spend some time at, at
relatively modest elevations, but

388
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:15,970
they get that higher altitude modest
hypoxia adaptation response.

389
00:26:15,970 --> 00:26:17,370
So there's some of that, and

390
00:26:17,370 --> 00:26:22,060
I've certainly noticed on other trips
coming back feeling va-va-voom.

391
00:26:22,060 --> 00:26:26,980
Being able to out-ride my cycling buddies
here by easy strides.

392
00:26:26,980 --> 00:26:29,060
I mean, I can just run away from them.

393
00:26:29,060 --> 00:26:31,110
From that adaptive response.

394
00:26:31,110 --> 00:26:36,930
The other thing that, that I've noticed
which actually was fairly carefully cat-,

